# Created field change · pocketbase pocketbase · Discussion #3248
created: 2023-09-03, last updated: 2026-04-16, [Read more](https://github.com/pocketbase/pocketbase/discussions/3248)

No, but you can add your own date field (eg. `submitted`/`published`) instead.
At the moment the system `created`/`updated` fields are automanaged and can't be modified with the web APIs (*this may change in the future*).
Alternatively you can attach to the record before create hook with Go or JS and manually set the `created` field with the submitted body data.
Here is an example with JS:
```
// pb_hooks/main.pb.js
onRecordBeforeCreateRequest((e) => {
const info = $apis.requestInfo(e.httpContext);
e.record.set('created', info.data.created);
})
```
