# How can I set default value of a field in pocketbase · pocketbase pocketbase · Discussion #2193
created: 2023-04-01, last updated: 2026-04-16, [Read more](https://github.com/pocketbase/pocketbase/discussions/2193)

You have access to the request context only in the `*Request` suffixed hooks (this is made more clear with the upcoming v0.23.0 APIs and new documentation).
...
```
onRecordBeforeCreateRequest((e) => {
// https://pocketbase.io/docs/js-routing/#retrieving-the-current-auth-state
const info = $apis.requestInfo(e.httpContext);
if (info.admin) {
return null // skip for admins
}
if (!info.authRecord) {
throw new UnauthorizedError()
}
e.record.set("owner", info.authRecord.id)
}, "yourCollection")
```
With v0.23.0 the above could be written like this:
```
// with v0.23.0 this also runs BEFORE the validations,
// so you can mark the "owner" relation field as non-empty from the collection field options
// and it will do the necessary checks for you
onRecordCreateRequest((e) => {
if (e.hasSuperuserAuth()) {
return e.next() // skip for superusers
}
e.record.set("owner", e.auth?.id)
e.next();
}, "yourCollection")
```

